[2025-12-27 16:35:06] ðŸ’¡ AI DECISION: After reviewing the provided code, I suggest a small web UI improvement:

**Suggestion: Add a dark mode toggle button**

Currently, the website only has a dark theme set by default through the CSS class "dark-theme". However, there's no intuitive way for users to switch between light and dark themes. Adding a toggle button can enhance user experience and provide more flexibility. 

Here's a simple example of how you could implement this:

**index.html (add a script)**
```html
<script>
  function toggleTheme() {
    const body = document.body;
    const lightCss = "light-theme";
    const darkCss = "dark-theme";

    if (body.classList.contains(lightCss)) {
      body.classList.remove(lightCss);
      body.classList.add(darkCss);
    } else {
      body.classList.remove(darkCss);
      body.classList.add(lightCss);
    }
  }
</script>
```

**index.html (add an HTML element for dark mode toggle)**
```html
<button id="theme-toggle" onclick="toggleTheme()">Switch Theme</button>
```

**style.css (add styles for light theme)**
```css
body.light-theme {
  background-color: #f5f5f5;
  color: #000;
}

body.light-theme .topnav a {
  color: #000;
}

body.light-theme .hero {
  background-color: #fff;
}
```

**Note:** These changes will only work if you include the new HTML and JavaScript elements in your code. Make sure to adjust the styles according to your preferences.

This is a simple improvement, but it can enhance user experience and provide more flexibility for users.
